rch of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705202,"age":119,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When John Small II was born in 1439, in Devon, England, his father, John Small, was 20 and his mother, Mrs. John Small, was 18. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Jane Holway. He died in England."},"et":{"1439–":"1439–Surnud","1439–Male":"1439–Surnud","1442–Female":"1442–Surnud","1430–1459":"1430–1459","–Male":"Surnud","1419–Male":"1419–Surnud","1422–Female":"1422–Surnud","1558":"1558","1459":"1459","1455":"1455","1422":"1422","1442":"1442","1430":"1430","1419":"1419","1439":"1439","1549":"1549","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1439–":"1439–Kuollut","1439–Male":"1439–Kuollut","1442–Female":"1442–Kuollut","1430–1459":"1430–1459","–Male":"Kuollut","1419–Male":"1419–Kuollut","1422–Female":"1422–Kuollut","1558":"1558","1459":"1459","1455":"1455","1422":"1422","1442":"1442","1430":"1430","1419":"1419","1439":"1439","1549":"1549","England":"England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1439–":"1439–Décédé","1439–Male":"1439–Décédé","1442–Female":"1442–Décédée","1430–1459":"1430–1459","–Male":"Décédé","1419–Male":"1419–Décédé","1422–Female":"1422–Décédée","1558":"1558","1459":"1459","1455":"1455","1422":"1422","1442":"1442","1430":"1430","1419":"1419","1439":"1439","1549":"1549","England":"Angleterre","Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque John Small II est né en 14